Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "ogromne" in different forms and positions:

1. Ogromne su šanse da ćeš dobiti posao. (Adjective - "The chances are huge that you will get the job.")
2. Ona je imala ogromnu količinu hrane u frižideru. (Adjective - "She had a huge amount of food in the fridge.")
3. Ogromne su mi misli u glavi, ne znam kako da se snađem. (Adjective - "I have huge thoughts in my head, I don't know how to cope.")
4. Da li si primetio *ogromnog* psa kako trči niz ulicu? (Adjective - Accusative case - "Did you notice the huge dog running down the street?")
5. Pogledaj koliko *ogromnih* knjiga ima u ovoj biblioteci. (Adjective - Genitive case - "Look at how many huge books there are in this library.")
6. Bilo je *ogromno* zadovoljstvo raditi s tobom. (Adverb - "It was hugely enjoyable to work with you.")
7. *Ogromnoj* količini novca nije mogao da odoli. (Adjective - Dative case - "He couldn't resist the huge amount of money.")
8. Videla sam *ogromnu* stvar u parku, ali ne znam šta je to bilo. (Adjective - Nominative case - "I saw a huge thing in the park, but I don't know what it was.")

